.TH "iwpm_get_remote_info" 9 "iwpm_get_remote_info" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
iwpm_get_remote_info \- Get the remote connecting peer address info
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" iwpm_get_remote_info
.BI "(struct sockaddr_storage *mapped_loc_addr "  ","
.BI "struct sockaddr_storage *mapped_rem_addr "  ","
.BI "struct sockaddr_storage *remote_addr "  ","
.BI "u8 nl_client "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "mapped_loc_addr" 12
Mapped local address of the listening peer
.IP "mapped_rem_addr" 12
Mapped remote address of the connecting peer
.IP "remote_addr" 12
To store the remote address of the connecting peer
.IP "nl_client" 12
The index of the netlink client
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
The remote address info is retrieved and provided to the client in
the remote_addr. After that it is removed from the hash table
